<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,261,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was first recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[707,775,261,287]" name="South Korea" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">Korea</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Esaki, T. &amp; Ito, S." box="[819,1031,260,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567" refId="ref9132" refString="Esaki, T. &amp; Ito, S. (1954) A tentative catalogue of Jassoidea of Japan, and her adjacent territories. The Japan Society for the Promotion of Science, Tokyo, 315 pp." type="book" year="1954">Esaki &amp; Ito (1954)</bibRefCitation>
who did not list any voucher specimens or examine male genitalic characters, which are essential for accurate identification. Since then, it was cited by several authors from 
<collectingCountry box="[421,489,333,359]" name="South Korea" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ishihara, T." box="[503,668,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567" pagination="225 - 257" refId="ref9206" refString="Ishihara, T. (1961) Homoptera of Southeast Asia collected by the Osaka City University Biological Expedition to Southeast Asia 1957 - 58. Nature and Life in Southeast Asia, 1, 225 - 257." type="journal article" year="1961">Ishihara, 1961</bibRefCitation>
; Lee &amp; Kwon, 1977; Kwon 
<emphasis box="[982,1045,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="567">et. al.</emphasis>
1996; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kwon, Y. J. &amp; Huh, E. Y." box="[1115,1339,333,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="567" pagination="1 - 461" refId="ref9428" refString="Kwon, Y. J. &amp; Huh, E. Y. (2001) Suborder Auchenorrhyncha. Economic Insects of Korea 19. Insecta Koreana Suppliment, 26, 1 - 461." type="journal article" year="2001">Kwon &amp; Huh, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). We did not find any Korean specimens that could be identified as this species. Therefore, the presence of this species on the Korean peninsula is uncertain and needs confirmation because it may be confused with other allied species.
</paragraph>
